property_description: Welcome to a unique multi-unit opportunity in Sausalito. The main residence is 516 Olive, designed by John Carden Campbell of Campbell & Wong Architects in 1972. It has been thoughtfully updated, there are 2 BRs, 2 BAs, office area w/laundry + 2-car garage. Primary suite opens to a courtyard & garden. Upper level is a spectacular open concept with 12-ft ceilings & huge windows w/views of Richardson Bay & Angel Island, beautiful built-ins, designer kitchen, front deck & rear patio for seamless indoor-outdoor living. With a blend of history & modern amenities, all the units interiors were extensively remodeled from 2012-2023, along with exterior landscaping, gardens & driveways. Adjacent is 518 Olive, an old fishing cottage that has been transformed into a chic 2-BD, 1-BA w/1-car garage. It features a remodeled kitchen, upgraded bath, new deck, fenced yard, high ceilings, wood-burning stove and bay views. 516A Olive is a legal ADU converted from an art studio w/full kitchen, full bath, laundry & private patio, a hip inspirational space. Ideally located with quick access to freeways & town to enjoy the Sausalito lifestyle. Whether seeking a multifamily compound or a primary residence with supplemental rental income, this opportunity offers timeless appeal.

property_description: Located a designated San Francisco landmark building, the Jackson Brewery Building, this true conversion condominium is in a small boutique building (8 units). This home offers original brick interior walls & industrial finishes including hardwood floors, tall ceilings, concrete details, steel beams, & wood windows that flood the open-concept space with western-facing natural light. Featuring a stylish kitchen with recessed halogen lighting, stone countertops, custom wine storage and stainless steel appliances, there is a raised bedroom space with outfitted closet, as well as a full bath with attached in-unit laundry & outfitted storage closet. This condominium features may finishes that remind you of a NYC SoHo-style loft conversion. There is a shared roof-top terrace with lounge areas, dining table and grill. There is a high-tech video entry system, key-security elevator and this unit includes 1-car assigned parking. Located near tech offices, restaurants, night-life, it offers easy highway access. This is a unique, historic, beautiful place to make your nest. Property is open concept, tax records indicate no bedroom nor bathroom count. Commerial space condo houses Basil Canteen Restaurant on Street level.

property_description: Fabulous condominium in the heart of Noe Valley! With a private entrance, this peaceful residence features dark hardwood flooring, beautiful moldings, and floor to ceiling windows. The heart of the home is the gorgeous kitchen/family room. The open kitchen centers around a large island with sink and chic pendants overhead, and the kitchen is equipped with deluxe stainless appliances, tile backsplash, and a built-in pantry cabinet. Off the kitchen is a dining area with sliding glass doors out to the deck, and an inviting living room with gas fireplace. Another set of sliding doors lead out to the serene, covered deck. There are two generous bedrooms, one with a bay window facing greenery, and the other with a large closet. Off the hallway is an additional office/nursery, plus an attractive bath with a double vanity and shower over tub, and a toilet room and sink next door. The unit also includes a substantial basement storage room. This boutique 2-unit building is located just blocks from 24th Street's dining and shopping.

property_description: Fabulous condominium in the heart of Noe Valley! With a private entrance, this peaceful residence features dark hardwood flooring, beautiful moldings, and floor to ceiling windows. The heart of the home is the gorgeous kitchen/family room. The open kitchen centers around a large island with sink and chic pendants overhead, and the kitchen is equipped with deluxe stainless appliances, tile backsplash, and a built-in pantry cabinet. Off the kitchen is a dining area with sliding glass doors out to the deck, and an inviting living room with gas fireplace. Another set of sliding doors lead out to the serene, covered deck. This private space is perfect for al fresco dining and entertaining in all seasons, and stairs lead down to the lovely backyard, boasting a fire pit and seating and dining areas. There are two generous bedrooms, one with a bay window facing greenery, and the other with a large closet. Off the hallway is an additional office/nursery, plus an attractive bath with a double vanity and shower over tub, and a toilet room and sink next door. The unit also includes a substantial basement storage room. This boutique 2-unit building is located just blocks from 24th Street's dining and shopping.
Kitchen Features: Quartz Counter, Pantry Closet, Island w/Sink, Island

Step inside to discover a meticulously maintained residence exuding pride of ownership. This charming abode offers ample space for relaxation & everyday living. The spacious living areas are bathed in natural light, creating an inviting atmosphere for hosting & quiet evenings at home. Notable updates include crown molding, updated windows & doors, sun tunnels & new fridge & tub. A Ring security system & outdoor outlets add modern convenience. The backyard features a patio deck, perfect for entertaining, & a hot tub for ultimate relaxation. The lush flowering landscaping adds to the home's charm & tranquility. The large lot provides room for outdoor enjoyment, whether you're entertaining guests, gardening, or basking in the tranquility of your surroundings. Park your vehicles with ease in the 2-car garage, & utilize the driveway for 2 additional cars. Nestled amidst serene streets, enjoy a peaceful retreat while still being close to the vibrant amenities of San Leandro. Enjoy a leisurely stroll to nearby Burrell Fields, indulge in retail therapy at Marina Square Shopping Center & stay active at the nearby 24-Hour Fitness.

property_description: Welcome to 119 Gennessee Street, a captivating elegantly renovated modern residence in the heart of San Francisco. Step through the mahogany exterior front door, you enter main floor that finished with European oak floors, and ceiling speakers. A stunning kitchen with custom cabinets and top-of-the-line Thermador appliances, microwave drawer, and wine cooler. The master bedroom on the main floor is equipped with his and her closets and an oversized bathroom featuring a freestanding tub, a shower, and double vanity, while the other main floor bedroom provides an inviting space facing the street. A bonus finished attic space for recreation. The lower floor offers 2 additional bedrooms, a sitting area, and a convenient wet bar with a second wine coolers, providing ample space for relaxation and entertaining. This home has been reimagined with level 4 finishes and underfloor radiant heating ensure a comfortable and refined living experience. Additional features include a tankless water heater, an EV charging outlet in the garage, and an epoxied garage. With a spacious low-maintenance backyard this home presents an irresistible opportunity for those seeking modern elegance in Sunnyside prime location.

highlights_text: 2 Bedrooms1 BathroomsStatus ActiveSingle FamilyMLS# 424044655
property_description: Incredible development opportunity in Corona Heights! 260 Castro St has approved plans that are paid for and ready to be picked up from DBI (per seller). This parcel must be sold and developed with the adjacent parcel which also has approved plans, 262 Castro St. This double lot development has architectural plans crafted by Geddes Ulinskas Architects and calls for the development of four residences totaling 7, 828 sq. ft.: a) two 3-bedroom condominiums at 1, 963 sq. ft. and 1, 787 sq. ft., b) one 2-bedroom standalone single family home cottage at 1, 680 sq. ft., and c) one 3-bedroom single-family home at 2, 398 sq. ft. The homes will include Downtown VIEWS as well as 1-car parking for each home. Roof decks, terraces, and gardens are included in the plans. A 2-bedroom, 1-bathroom single family home currently sits at the front of 260 Castro St, and a 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom single family cottage sits at the rear of the parcel of 262 Castro St. Located in a highly-sought after location at the axis of Corona Heights, The Castro, and Duboce Triangle, the location of this opportunity affords the developer to command a premium price for the completed homes. The full construction package includes shoring and interior design plans. Images are digital renderings, buyers to investigate.

property_description: Step through the lush, garden patio to this freestanding, bi-level cottage. Windows on all four sides flood the space with light and outlooks are full of greenery and mature palms. Set back from the street with a secure, locked gated entrance for added security. The first level welcomes you with a comfortable living room and gas fireplace, a fully equipped kitchen with a new gas range, dishwasher & washer/dryer, plus a renovated full bathroom. The upper level holds the 2 bedrooms and a renovated half bath. A ladder in the primary bedroom leads to an additional storage space coupled with a built-in safe. New light fixtures, hardwood floors, charming period details and recent seismic upgrade to front building that houses the garage. One independent parking space in the garage. Living in the highly sought after Cow Hollow neighborhood offers a vibrant & coveted lifestyle in the heart of San Francisco. This upscale neighborhood offers easy access to the breathtaking waterfront of the Marina District, Crissy Field & Fort Mason. You'll also appreciate the proximity to the hip & bustling Union, Chestnut, and Fillmore streets, where you'll find an endless array of shops, restaurants, markets, bars, spas and many other entertainment options! Walk Score: 98 Bike Score: 92

property_description: From a coveted, elevated position, this outstanding 2, 815 Sq. Ft. (approximately) vintage Middle Ridge'' property showcases spectacular, far-reaching vistas that capture the stunning San Francisco skyline. Ideally situated, just a short stroll to the enchanting Village'' of downtown Mill Valley, it offers the new owners unending possibilities for modernization or fabrication of a dream'' home. Constructed in 1908 on a 9, 750 sq. ft. lot, it represents the early classic Mill Valley estates that were built on the most desirable sites with great consideration given to the warm weather zone near town. All day sun with southern exposure is yet another bonus factor to this extraordinary offering, long valued as Mill Valley's most sought-after street, the famed Summit Avenue. Enjoy the best of life as an integral part of the village, set amidst verdant Sequoia/Redwoods, with delightful upscale boutiques, cafes, restaurants, a gourmet grocery, movie theater, and the popular meeting place, Lytton Square also known as the Depot that unites the inhabitants.

property_description: Prestigious Pacific Heights location with stunning bay views on all levels define this extraordinary 7 bedroom, 7.5 bathroom residence. Designed by renowned San Francisco architect Bernard Joseph, the home's thoughtful layout spans three levels and seamlessly blends meticulous craftsmanship with modern luxury. The top and middle levels each offer full-floor homes with 3 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms (2 ensuite), formal living and dining rooms, and modern amenities. The top floor features a grand skylight, eat-in chef's kitchen, and an enclosed atrium. The middle floor boasts a fully remodeled kitchen with butler pantry. An exceptional 1 bed, 1.5 bath housekeeping unit includes a private entrance and opens onto a charming garden with bay views. The expansive rooftop deck and garden blend indoor and outdoor living, creating ideal spaces for entertaining or relaxing. An elevator provides convenient access to all three levels of the home. Situated on a coveted and level block of Pacific Avenue, this home sits on a wide and deep 37' x 128' lot. This is a rare opportunity to own a piece of San Francisco history, with unparalleled views and an impeccable design that stands the test of time.

highlights_text: 2 Bedrooms1 BathroomsStatus ActiveCondominiumMLS# 424043651
Parking Features: Garage Facing Front, Garage Door Opener
property_description: This top-floor Outer Richmond flat boasts modern contemporary living with a spacious floor plan and abundant light. The home features an updated kitchen, enhanced by white marble counters with a waterfall edge, stainless steel appliances, and a skylight. There is a large dining room perfect for entertaining family and friends. A generous living area with a wood-burning fireplace and large, west-facing window. Two ample bedrooms and an updated bath with marble tile surround, clawfoot tub, and shower finish off the living area. At the garage level, there is a big storage room, washer/dryer, 1 car parking, and a shared rear patio. Super low HOA dues averaging $152 a month. Cross Fulton and you are in the historic GG Park. Just a few blocks west to Ocean Beach, surfs up! Near Butterfly Joint and great restaurants and shops on Balboa like The Laundromat, as well as easy access to popular Sunset eateries like Hook Fish, Outerlands, and Palm City.

property_description: This polished 3-bedroom, 2-bath co-op unit in a prestigious 12 unit building, blends modern elegance with historic charm, offering a truly unique and luxurious living experience in desirable Pacific Heights. An open floor plan connects the gracious foyer, living room and dining room with direct access to an inviting sunroom & private deck. Chef's kitchen boasts high-end stainless-steel appliances, sleek granite countertops, custom cabinetry, inspiring your inner culinary passion. Convenient butler's pantry off the kitchen. Retreat to primary suite with walk-in closet, spa-like en-suite bathroom. The third bedroom is equally inviting as a home office/den.Features modern conveniences of in-unit laundry, hardwood floors, recessed lighting, and ample storage space. Relax on your private deck, perfect for morning coffee/evening cocktails. Elevator to garage pkg & storage. Access San Francisco's finest dining, shopping, and cultural landmarks. Enjoy convenience of nearby Lafayette Park, Whole Foods, & bustling Fillmore Street. HOA dues include heat, water, trash, maintenance, resident manager, and insurance. New roof in 2023 and elevator upgrade in 2021. With its blend of classic charm and modern amenities, this unit is a rare find in one of the city's most coveted neighborhoods.

highlights_text: 2 Bedrooms2 BathroomsStatus ActiveSingle FamilyMLS# 424044656
property_description: Incredible development opportunity in Corona Heights! 262 Castro St has approved plans that are paid for and ready to be picked up from DBI (per seller). This parcel must be sold and developed with the adjacent parcel which also has approved plans, 260 Castro St. This double lot development has architectural plans crafted by Geddes Ulinskas Architects and calls for the development of four residences totaling 7, 828 sq. ft.: a) two 3-bedroom condominiums at 1, 963 sq. ft. and 1, 787 sq. ft., b) one 2-bedroom standalone single family home cottage at 1, 680 sq. ft., and c) one 3-bedroom single-family home at 2, 398 sq. ft. The homes will include Downtown VIEWS as well as 1-car parking for each home. Roof decks, terraces, and gardens are included in the plans. A 2-bedroom, 1-bathroom single family home currently sits at the front of 260 Castro St, and a 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom single family cottage sits at the rear of the parcel of 262 Castro St. Located in a highly-sought after location at the axis of Corona Heights, The Castro, and Duboce Triangle, the location of this opportunity affords the developer to command a premium price for the completed homes. The full construction package includes shoring and interior design plans. Images are digital renderings, buyers to investigate.

highlights_text: 2 Bedrooms1 Bathrooms1355 sq ftStatus ActiveSingle FamilyMLS# 424031729
Main Level: Living Room, Kitchen, Full Bath(s), Dining Room, Bedroom(s)
Appliances: Hood Over Range, Free Standing Refrigerator, Free Standing Gas Range, Disposal, Dishwasher
Parking Features: Side-by-Side, Interior Access, Garage Facing Front, Garage Door Opener
property_description: 500 Ellington, in the same family for nearly 50 years, has been thoughtfully renewed inside and out, and is ready for its next caretakers. This turnkey 2-bedroom / 1-bathroom single-family home occupies a corner lot. Vintage terrazzo steps lead to a foyer with coat closet. The front-facing living room features corner windows with views from Sutro Tower to McLaren Park, and the formal dining room is great to gather for festive and everyday meals. The eat-in kitchen has brand-new stainless-steel appliances, abundant cabinets, and counter space on every wall. Enjoy peaceful neighborhood views and space for a small island or breakfast nook. At the rear of the home, find two spacious bedrooms, each with good natural light, large closets, and refinished wood floors. The adjacent renovated bathroom and a linen closet complete this level. Internal stairs lead to the lower level, with 2 side-by-side garage spots, a deep storage closet, and a laundry area with sink. This floor also includes a generous bonus room - use it as an office, playroom, guest space, or base for future expansion. The backyard includes a patio with planter beds and peekaboo views of Salesforce Tower. Easy access to the freeway and public transit, Mission Street shops and restaurants, and schools and playgrounds.

property_description: Compass Commercial is pleased to present for sale, 4505 - 4507 Mission Street, in San Francisco is a 5 unit mixed use building in the Mission Terrace/Excelsior District. The property has three leased units and two pending lease units, leaving the option open for a buyer to occupy units or lease to generate more income. This is a two story walk up that also includes a back yard. The ground floor retail is leased on a month to month basis. The 2nd Floor has two studio's and two single room occupant with a shared bathroom. The units are all separately metered w/ PG&E. This is a prominent location on a main commercial corridor w/ many neighboring retail, service, and restaurant businesses. McLaren Park, Bart, and Freeway Entrances are close by. highlights_text: 2 Bedrooms2 Bathrooms1059 sq ftStatus ActiveCondominiumMLS# 424045624
Appliances: Free Standing Refrigerator, Free Standing Electric Range
property_description: Come visit this panoramic view residence atop San Francisco's prestigious Nob Hill. You'll be greeted by views of our City's most iconic landmarks out of the condo's floor-to-ceiling windows. From the waters of the Bay, to Nob Hill's stunningly beautiful architectural treasures, beyond to the Downtown skyline, & even a peek of the Bay Bridge; the views rival those of condominiums priced at millions more. In fact, the price-point & value of this two bedroom, two bath condo are unmatched. With a creative vision, this Gramercy Towers jewel can be transformed into a sweet high-rise sanctuary, worthy of the heritage & history of its Nob Hill environment. The Gramercy Towers provides premium services & amenities for its residents, including a front desk concierge, a fitness center, indoor pool, jetted hot tub, men's & women's locker rooms, spacious lobby, gated courtyard, & more. The best of SF is at your doorstep with Nob Hill's year-round event programming, the iconic Cable Cars, & much more. Plus, the Gramercy is just blocks away from downtown, Union Square, Chinatown & North Beach, grocery stores, parks, restaurants, cafs, & health care services; making this apartment a quintessential San Francisco home. Please note that the furnishings used in the photos are virtually rendered.
View Description: Downtown, City Lights, City, Bay Bridge, Bay

property_description: Welcome to a unique multi-unit opportunity in Sausalito. The main residence is 516 Olive, designed by John Carden Campbell of Campbell & Wong Architects in 1972. It has been thoughtfully updated, there are 2 BRs, 2 BAs, office area w/laundry + 2-car garage. Primary suite opens to a courtyard & garden. Upper level is a spectacular open concept with 12-ft ceilings & huge windows w/views of Richardson Bay & Angel Island, beautiful built-ins, designer kitchen, front deck & rear patio for seamless indoor-outdoor living. With a blend of history & modern amenities, all the units interiors were extensively remodeled from 2012-2023, along with exterior landscaping, gardens & driveways. Adjacent is 518 Olive, an old fishing cottage that has been transformed into a chic 2-BD, 1-BA w/1-car garage. It features a remodeled kitchen, upgraded bath, new deck, fenced yard, high ceilings, wood-burning stove and bay views. 516A Olive is a legal ADU converted from an art studio w/full kitchen, full bath, laundry & private patio, a hip inspirational space. Ideally located with quick access to freeways & town to enjoy the Sausalito lifestyle. Whether seeking a multifamily compound or a primary residence with supplemental rental income, this opportunity offers timeless appeal.

property_description: This large 3-bedroom, 2-bath condo combines a gracious scale with beautiful architectural details. The inviting front steps lead through fluted columns to the sheltered entry. From the welcoming foyer you are drawn to the living room, which spans the front of the home. It is flooded with natural light from the oversized bay windows overlooking the verdant street trees. The living room and adjacent dining room each have fireplaces with stunning mantelpieces; both are comfortable rooms for daily living, but also lend themselves to entertaining on an epic scale. The large formal dining room has stately built-ins and is ideal for gracious dinner parties. The recently renovated eat-in kitchen has ample cabinetry, counter space and stainless steel appliances. A full bath is conveniently located off the hall which leads to the three bedrooms. The primary suite, with a private, en-suite bath, overlooks the garden and green belt. The second bedroom also overlooks the backyard and is connected to the third by a passage with a conveniently located vanity room with washbasin. In-unit laundry and additional secure storage offer added convenience. Golden Gate Park, Buena Vista Park, Haight and Cole Valley are all within a few blocks.

The primary bedroom, with fabulous views, has a spacious and timeless bathroom featuring richly-veined stones and a modern glass enclosed shower, as well as a walk-in closet with ample hanging space. The second bedroom is a good size, along with similarly stunning outlooks. This bedroom is served by a full bathroom that doubles as a guest bath, also with classic stone finishes and featuring a shower over tub. 1-car parking in the secure garage, storage, and a 24-hour doorman and professional management, make this the epitome of luxury living, close to the vibrant shops and restaurants of Russian Hill.

The main living area, adorned with 14-foot ceilings of gorgeous natural wood beams and anchored by original brick fireplace, is directly off of the kitchen and dining space. property_description: 1959, the year 3431-3433 22nd Street was constructed, was marked by a modern aesthetic in architecture, with buildings having smooth, flattened facades, often demarcated by different planes rather than physical decoration. Located in a row of housing likely built around the same time, this building is no exception. The decorative aspect of the faade is an inset vertical rectangle, highlighted by color, which suggests a certain separation of space within. The current owners took the interior down to the studs and recreated a modern space, but this time with more open entertaining rooms, separated by an arch that mimics the kitchen island lights and back-splash tiles. The curves both disrupt and complement the angular lines of the interior. Two generous bedrooms overlook the rear shared yard with the spacious hallway bathroom having a mirror-like effect caused by the floor-to-ceiling tile on the right wall as you enter. On the garage level is a bonus space used by the current owners as an office with an updated half-bath, all permitted in 2010. The shared yard includes a common gas burner, grill and sink. The location is exceptional, whether walking, biking, or driving to one's chosen destination.
Association Fee Includes: Maintenance Grounds, Insurance on Structure, Common Areas

property_description: Once-in-a-generation opportunity to own this iconic 6 unit Mediterranean Villa in historic Old Town Sausalito! Perched on a coveted corner lot in prime location overlooking San Francisco Bay, this 10 BD, 8 BA property is minutes from GG Bridge and City. Stroll by Bay to ferry, cafes, boutiques. Property has 2 vintage circa 1920 buildings each with 3 units. Six units total (four 1 BD/1 BA top floor units; two 3 BD/2 BA middle floor units). All units have views, original features, hardwood floors, separate PG&E/water meters. Four with fireplaces. Clay tiled roof & archways lead to outdoor patio connecting the buildings. Top floor units have entries off quiet cul-de-sac. Stunning views of Angel Island, City & Alcatraz from top floor east-facing units. There's more! A secluded courtyard; 3 expansive garages; office; storage units, & laundry facilities. Ideally situated in a charming, residential neighborhood, 3 blocks from Sausalito's world-renowned waterfront, Southview park and Swede's beach. Endless opportunities for savvy investors - possible lot split; condo convert; additional income from storage units & repurposing garages (buyer to investigate options). 4.62% cap rate before additional income potential. This trophy property held with the same owner for 25 years. Must see!

property_description: Spectacular SOMA tri-level live work loft. Light filled gallery-like living space with nearly 17 ft ceilings and dramatic west facing windows, window seating bench, wood floors and corner fireplace. Updated kitchen has a window over the sink and features stone counters and new stainless appliances. Half bath and in unit laundry closet with new appliances completes the main level. Upper level loft primary bedroom with east facing windows, en suite bath, closet with organizers and adjacent generous sized sitting area that could also serve as office space. Ground floor patio level has second bedroom/office with en suite bath and magical private patio providing indoor outdoor living. Truly versatile tri-level floor plan that affords privacy with separation of spaces for living and working. Rarely available feature is direct access from the private garage into the unit. Semi-private common entrance shared with only 3 other units. 15 Lucerne is on a lightly trafficked cul de sac alley street. Amenities nearby include Trader Joe's, Whole Foods, Costco, Caltrain, restaurants and cafes, easy access to downtown and freeway, Yerba Buena Center for Arts, SF Museum of Modern Art, Mission Creek Park and Oracle Park. Come see for yourself this beautiful and unique live work loft.
Laundry Features: Washer Included, Laundry Closet, Dryer Included
